{
  "stem": "25639.9",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was very good at taking orders still in those days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we were taken to a ferry boat, and we crossed the body of water separating Denmark from Sweden called the Oresund.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we crossed the Oresund to Malmo, Sweden, where they fumigated us with DDT, and we showered.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We received new clothes and we started a new life there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And since we numbered into the thousands, they separate-- separated us into the various communities.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- the distributed us into the various communities of the area, and I was sent to Landskrona, which is a charming little town in southern Sweden.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "From there you could actually see across the Oresund over to Copenhagen-- [SWEDISH], as we call it in Swedish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there we-- there in Landskrona we were-- they let the schools out early to make room for all of us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They placed mattresses on the floors of the classes and we-- there were nurses and doctors.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were very-- going through a process of examination to separate the contagious-- those who had contagious diseases from those of us who had other serious ailments.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was very happy to learn that I had no contagious disease and that-- but just vitamin deficiency problems and 17-- 17 cavities in my teeth needed immediate care.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- my leg was as a result of vitamin-- this-- this vitamin deficiency problem, which really refused to heal for months and months.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were-- until my body received enough nutrition, it-- it refused to heal.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It-- it took approximately seven, eight months for them to heal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I still have-- I call them volcanoes-- on my right leg, these-- these-- these marks and bumps where-- where I-- where these scars were.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Arrived-- I arrived in Malmo on May 3, 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
